1
00:00:16,350 --> 00:00:17,960
Beijing isn't beyond the law.

2
00:00:18,670 --> 00:00:19,550
Don't worry.

3
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:21,710
I'll get justice for you.

4
00:00:22,830 --> 00:00:24,600
You're just a cop.

5
00:00:25,670 --> 00:00:26,600
They've all been

6
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,480
working together for years.

7
00:00:30,670 --> 00:00:31,830
You can't beat them.

8
00:00:31,830 --> 00:00:33,650
How do you know
an ant can't bring down a tree?

9
00:00:33,650 --> 00:00:34,800
=Cases Between Us=

10
00:00:34,810 --> 00:00:36,150
Those scum

11
00:00:36,430 --> 00:00:38,240
=Episode 13=
have been feeding on women.

12
00:00:39,150 --> 00:00:40,840
Even if it costs me my life,

13
00:00:41,430 --> 00:00:43,070
I'll fight them to the bitter end.

14
00:01:21,590 --> 00:01:23,200
I mean it.

15
00:02:04,710 --> 00:02:06,040
Going in head-on like this

16
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,070
is too risky, isn't it?

17
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:08,000
I gave Xie Qing my word.

18
00:02:08,010 --> 00:02:09,168
And if we don't wipe them out,

19
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:10,150
they'll come back again.

20
00:02:10,150 --> 00:02:10,430
But...

21
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:11,776
Stop trying to talk me out of it.

22
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:13,800
Chief Yuan,

23
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,460
the commissioner wants to see you.

24
00:02:18,576 --> 00:02:20,000
Get Division Four together.

25
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,150
You brief everyone on the plan.

26
00:02:21,150 --> 00:02:21,590
Yes, sir.

27
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:22,680
Wait...

28
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,030
Yang Dezhi.

29
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:28,910
Why do you all

30
00:02:28,910 --> 00:02:30,030
listen to everything he says?

31
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:31,840
Do we?

32
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:32,430
You do.

33
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:35,100
To be honest,

34
00:02:35,420 --> 00:02:36,900
it wasn't until Chief Yuan showed up

35
00:02:36,900 --> 00:02:38,020
that I learned

36
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:40,340
what a real cop is supposed to be.

37
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:44,020
He's just another glory hound.

38
00:02:44,260 --> 00:02:45,140
All of you

39
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:46,992
are nothing but stepping stones
on his way up.

40
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:48,020
Young Master Zhao,

41
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:49,260
you can insult me,

42
00:02:49,260 --> 00:02:50,432
but don't insult our chief.

43
00:02:51,056 --> 00:02:53,340
Hadn't he had you buy up
all those special editions?

44
00:02:54,460 --> 00:02:55,140
Special editions?

45
00:02:55,380 --> 00:02:56,140
Yeah.

46
00:02:58,180 --> 00:02:59,420
You've got him all wrong.

47
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,180
That day he got back,

48
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:02,780
he yelled at his father
for five minutes.

49
00:03:03,060 --> 00:03:03,740
It was his father

50
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:05,620
who bought up every last copy in town.

51
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:10,020
What about

52
00:03:10,340 --> 00:03:11,300
the photo in the paper?

53
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,944
He had the editor take it out,
didn't he?

54
00:03:13,260 --> 00:03:14,620
He was protecting you.

55
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:16,260
It involved powerful people.

56
00:03:16,304 --> 00:03:17,800
He didn't want you getting targeted.

57
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:19,180
Division Four, assemble.

58
00:03:19,330 --> 00:03:19,940
- Yes.
- Yes.

59
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:26,060
He's trying to play the hero.

60
00:03:26,860 --> 00:03:28,500
I don't need his protection.

61
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:36,340
(Integrity and Honesty)

62
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:39,700
Enough

63
00:03:40,304 --> 00:03:41,300
with the Eight Alleys.

64
00:03:41,620 --> 00:03:42,900
It ends here,

65
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:43,500
all right?

66
00:03:44,020 --> 00:03:45,060
Is that your order?

67
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:47,540
It's

68
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,660
what everyone wants.

69
00:03:49,940 --> 00:03:52,140
You caught the killer.

70
00:03:52,620 --> 00:03:54,580
The people who deserved to die are dead.

71
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:56,460
Close the case.

72
00:03:56,980 --> 00:03:57,580
How about this?

73
00:03:57,980 --> 00:03:59,780
I'll put you in for a commendation.

74
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:01,940
Have some tea.

75
00:04:02,980 --> 00:04:04,220
I'm not after a medal.

76
00:04:05,860 --> 00:04:06,700
What?

77
00:04:08,060 --> 00:04:09,420
Not after a medal?

78
00:04:10,740 --> 00:04:11,300
I know.

79
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:14,100
You're new
and need something to prove yourself.

80
00:04:14,740 --> 00:04:15,420
I get it.

81
00:04:15,488 --> 00:04:17,008
I just want to get rid of the evil.

82
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:21,380
The ones we can see
and the ones we can't.

83
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:31,020
Young man,

84
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:34,140
it's good to have ideals.

85
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:36,100
But...

86
00:04:36,620 --> 00:04:38,180
do you really think

87
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:41,900
you can arrest them all yourself?

88
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:43,420
I won't know unless I try.

89
00:04:43,420 --> 00:04:44,380
You can afford to try.

90
00:04:44,380 --> 00:04:45,620
Can they?

91
00:04:45,620 --> 00:04:46,900
When you're playing the hero,

92
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:48,780
have you stopped to think
about the men outside?

93
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:51,380
Every one of them
has a family depending on them.

94
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:52,580
However,

95
00:04:53,380 --> 00:04:56,820
they don't have a father like yours.

96
00:04:56,820 --> 00:04:57,260
He's him.

97
00:04:57,260 --> 00:04:58,060
I'm me.

98
00:04:58,160 --> 00:04:59,900
I can do without a father like that.

99
00:05:00,660 --> 00:05:01,420
Stop right there!

100
00:05:16,780 --> 00:05:19,620
They've already shown us

101
00:05:19,980 --> 00:05:22,580
every courtesy.

102
00:05:23,980 --> 00:05:24,740
This is for you.

103
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:27,300
I know you're not in it for the money.

104
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:29,900
But if you refuse this gesture,

105
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:32,900
I'm afraid not even your father
will be able to protect you.

106
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:54,220
Come. Give me a hand.

107
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:55,060
Come on.

108
00:05:55,060 --> 00:05:55,740
Fall in.

109
00:06:02,048 --> 00:06:04,112
I know every one of you
has a family to support.

110
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:06,256
It wasn't easy to land a job
at the police department.

111
00:06:06,910 --> 00:06:08,620
So today's operation is voluntary.

112
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:10,900
If you're coming with me, step forward.

113
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:13,060
If not, I won't hold it against you.

114
00:06:20,816 --> 00:06:22,432
What are you all standing around for?

115
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:23,340
Move.

116
00:06:30,336 --> 00:06:31,940
I see. The Jingshi Police Department

117
00:06:31,940 --> 00:06:33,300
is nothing but a bunch of cowards.

118
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:40,780
Every one of you is spineless.

119
00:06:40,816 --> 00:06:41,980
Calling you a bunch of losers

120
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:43,330
would be giving you too much credit.

121
00:06:43,340 --> 00:06:44,300
What's wrong with you?

122
00:06:45,660 --> 00:06:47,460
You see innocent girls getting abused,

123
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:49,340
and you all hide like tortoises.

124
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:50,940
Are you even men?

125
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:00,860
Oh, please.

126
00:07:00,860 --> 00:07:01,220
Uh...

127
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:02,100
Shut your mouth!

128
00:07:02,192 --> 00:07:03,580
I can't stand by and do nothing.

129
00:07:03,810 --> 00:07:05,620
Who's to say I won't be next tomorrow?

130
00:07:21,008 --> 00:07:22,420
If you're a man, come with us.

131
00:07:28,020 --> 00:07:28,900
Men,

132
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:30,380
what are we waiting for?

133
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:32,680
Let's do this.

134
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,700
- Worst case, we lose our jobs.
- Let's go.

135
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:37,820
You...

136
00:07:38,780 --> 00:07:39,780
Have you lost your minds?

137
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:59,380
(Jingshi Police Department)

138
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:21,660
Hello?

139
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:41,060
Search.

140
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:42,800
- Come with me.
- Search.

141
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:43,460
Move.

142
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:53,620
Nothing here.

143
00:08:53,620 --> 00:08:54,180
Chief.

144
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:55,460
- Nobody.
- Nothing.

145
00:09:10,141 --> 00:09:10,901
Get down!

146
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:17,740
Yuan Hong.

147
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:19,540
Yuan Hong!

148
00:10:22,140 --> 00:10:22,860
Yuan Hong!

149
00:10:31,790 --> 00:10:32,500
Yuan Hong!

150
00:10:33,020 --> 00:10:33,700
Yuan Hong!

151
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:35,580
Stay with me.

152
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:41,700
Stay with me.

153
00:10:41,940 --> 00:10:42,620
Yuan Hong!

154
00:10:44,860 --> 00:10:45,660
Yuan Hong!

155
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:58,620
Back from the dead?

156
00:10:59,580 --> 00:11:01,100
You are.

157
00:11:01,340 --> 00:11:02,580
I'm not dead.

158
00:11:02,980 --> 00:11:04,060
When did you wake up?

159
00:11:06,210 --> 00:11:07,560
With your driving skills,

160
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,540
you could wake the dead.

161
00:11:15,460 --> 00:11:16,620
You're hurt?

162
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:18,620
Are you okay?

163
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:19,940
I'm fine.

164
00:11:19,940 --> 00:11:20,860
It's just a scratch.

165
00:11:21,460 --> 00:11:22,260
Not like you.

166
00:11:22,288 --> 00:11:23,792
One little blast, and you passed out.

167
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:29,500
You.

168
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:30,140
Pay up.

169
00:11:32,340 --> 00:11:33,540
You scared me!

170
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:34,500
Pay up!

171
00:11:45,744 --> 00:11:46,740
Where are the gold bars?

172
00:11:47,420 --> 00:11:48,260
What gold bars?

173
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:49,780
The ones you used to bribe me.

174
00:11:49,952 --> 00:11:51,060
What are you talking about?

175
00:11:51,060 --> 00:11:52,740
I don't understand.

176
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:56,260
Don't believe me?

177
00:11:56,940 --> 00:11:58,464
Fine. Go ahead. Search the place.

178
00:11:58,768 --> 00:12:00,400
Search the place however you want.

179
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:05,500
You'll pay for this one day.

180
00:12:09,940 --> 00:12:11,820
Don't start with me.

181
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:32,940
We found the hideout

182
00:12:33,380 --> 00:12:34,540
and arrested all of them.

183
00:12:34,940 --> 00:12:36,740
All the girls have been rescued.

184
00:12:37,620 --> 00:12:38,300
Really?

185
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:39,940
Really.

186
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:45,860
Yuan Hong said you like Coke.

187
00:12:46,420 --> 00:12:48,060
I warmed it up for you.

188
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,180
It's healthier.

189
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:56,940
Why didn't he come himself?

190
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:58,700
You know what he's like.

191
00:12:58,700 --> 00:12:59,620
He's a snowflake.

192
00:12:59,620 --> 00:13:00,820
He's got a minor injury.

193
00:13:10,620 --> 00:13:11,700
We've taken Xiaoman

194
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:12,980
to your parents

195
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:14,380
just like you asked.

196
00:13:15,260 --> 00:13:16,420
We wrote them a letter.

197
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:19,420
They'll teach her to read,

198
00:13:19,740 --> 00:13:22,460
and later enroll her in a girls' school.

199
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:25,300
We'll hire the best lawyer in Beijing

200
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:26,180
to defend you.

201
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:29,060
Your story's been published, too.

202
00:13:29,740 --> 00:13:31,140
The public is on your side.

203
00:13:31,808 --> 00:13:33,100
Your sentence should be lighter.

204
00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:39,100
I'm sorry.

205
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:41,620
Sorry?

206
00:13:42,380 --> 00:13:44,700
I thought you were just
another spoiled rich kid.

207
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:50,460
Then?

208
00:13:52,180 --> 00:13:54,220
You looked down on me?

209
00:13:54,460 --> 00:13:55,500
I didn't.

210
00:13:56,380 --> 00:13:57,260
It's okay.

211
00:13:57,500 --> 00:13:58,460
I'm used to it.

212
00:13:58,780 --> 00:14:00,580
That's what everyone thinks.

213
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:03,060
Still, it hasn't stopped me
from living life my way.

214
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:04,980
Don't mind it.

215
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:09,620
We'll be waiting for you.

216
00:14:36,780 --> 00:14:38,120
(The Law Brings Peace to the People)

217
00:14:38,130 --> 00:14:40,100
(Mercy Brings Them Comfort,
Uphold Virtue, Eradicate Evil)

218
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:51,740
You used to dislike me, didn't you?

219
00:14:52,140 --> 00:14:53,580
Why are you saying all this now?

220
00:14:55,420 --> 00:14:56,460
Yuan Hong told me

221
00:14:56,460 --> 00:14:59,060
you were his only friend in Britain.

222
00:14:59,460 --> 00:15:00,540
That makes you

223
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:01,820
half a friend of mine too.

224
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:03,660
Of course I'd help you.

225
00:15:08,220 --> 00:15:11,060
Are you close with Yuan Hong?

226
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:12,300
Of course.

227
00:15:14,020 --> 00:15:14,740
Do you think

228
00:15:17,020 --> 00:15:18,780
he sees you as a friend?

229
00:15:31,460 --> 00:15:32,740
I don't think so.

230
00:15:34,540 --> 00:15:37,140
There's one secret

231
00:15:37,140 --> 00:15:39,180
I bet you don't know.

232
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:42,860
So I'm one up on you.

233
00:15:50,420 --> 00:15:51,380
What secret?

234
00:15:55,340 --> 00:15:56,180
You haven't told me.

235
00:15:56,180 --> 00:15:57,392
How do you know I don't know it?

236
00:15:57,424 --> 00:15:57,940
Then tell me.

237
00:15:57,940 --> 00:15:58,500
Go on.

238
00:15:58,500 --> 00:15:59,060
Tell me.

239
00:16:01,420 --> 00:16:01,900
Come on.

240
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:25,980
Hello.

241
00:16:30,976 --> 00:16:32,050
What are you doing here?

242
00:16:32,980 --> 00:16:33,980
Can't I come?

243
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:35,180
If not, I'll leave.

244
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:40,500
You really want me to leave?

245
00:16:41,712 --> 00:16:44,160
Since I'm already here,
aren't you going to invite me in?

246
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:46,700
I'm already here,

247
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:47,220
you won't even

248
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:48,500
invite me in?

249
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,540
So rude.

250
00:16:57,580 --> 00:16:59,300
Planning to eat all night?

251
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:00,940
Even one bite

252
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:02,820
deserves a proper setup.

253
00:17:03,180 --> 00:17:04,300
Besides,

254
00:17:04,820 --> 00:17:05,700
we've solved

255
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:07,060
three cases together.

256
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:08,740
We still haven't
had a celebratory drink.

257
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:10,620
Try Scotch whiskey.

258
00:17:10,660 --> 00:17:11,780
Wasn't easy to get.

259
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:16,260
Enough.

260
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,488
I finished it all.

261
00:17:20,624 --> 00:17:21,620
I finished it all.

262
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:23,660
Wait. That's hardly a toast.

263
00:17:23,940 --> 00:17:25,340
Xie Qing said you could really drink.

264
00:17:26,540 --> 00:17:28,380
Did she also tell you I can drink,

265
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:29,300
I just don't like to?

266
00:17:29,344 --> 00:17:30,640
Drinking clouds your judgment.

267
00:17:31,860 --> 00:17:33,100
Tomorrow's our day off.

268
00:17:33,940 --> 00:17:35,060
Besides,

269
00:17:35,136 --> 00:17:36,700
you'll drink with her, but not with me?

270
00:17:38,580 --> 00:17:40,260
What did she tell you?

271
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:42,540
Are you drinking or not?

272
00:17:47,020 --> 00:17:47,620
Fine.

273
00:18:04,220 --> 00:18:05,300
Let me ask you something.

274
00:18:05,980 --> 00:18:06,740
Well,

275
00:18:06,740 --> 00:18:08,620
if she'd really stabbed me that night,

276
00:18:09,380 --> 00:18:10,420
what would you have done?

277
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:12,180
If she'd really stabbed you,

278
00:18:12,180 --> 00:18:13,648
I'd have called it a public service.

279
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:14,820
You're unbelievable.

280
00:18:15,180 --> 00:18:16,620
But I knew she wouldn't.

281
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,500
And if she had?

282
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:20,380
If she had,

283
00:18:21,740 --> 00:18:23,220
I'd put you in for a commendation

284
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:26,700
and ride your sacrifice
all the way to a promotion.

285
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:30,380
You?

286
00:18:31,540 --> 00:18:33,540
If all you wanted was rank and fortune,

287
00:18:33,616 --> 00:18:35,420
you wouldn't have defied
the commissioner.

288
00:18:37,820 --> 00:18:38,980
Then what am I doing it for?

289
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:47,260
That's exactly what I'm curious about.

290
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:56,620
(End of Episode 13)

